com.uce.userlab.haptics.HL
Interface HLEventCallback

public interface HLEventCallback

This Interface should be implemented by Objects that wish to listen to events from the HL toolkit. You will be forced by the compiler to implement all the methods but some may not be of use to you, ignore these.

Method Detail

HL_EVENT_MOTION

void HL_EVENT_MOTION(int shapeId,
                     int thread,
                     HLCache cache,
                     java.lang.Object[] data)
This method is called when a motion event is fired

Parameters:
shapeId - The Identifier for the shape that the event has been fired for
thread - The thread that the event has been fired from
cache - The Cache object that store parameter values from when the event fired
data - An array of objects that have been set to be passed at event callback scheduling
